role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 05, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104xhy1665702879518.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xhy1665702879518.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/xhy1665702879518.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"xhy1665702879518\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n           \n Uniface and the Registry\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">On Windows, Uniface saves logical printers, application layout state, command line history, and other settings in the Windows Registry.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xhy1665702879518__section_w7247ab1b5b1_w7248ab1b5_w7249ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d499323e51\">\n            \n Default Registry Locations\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xhy1665702879518__p_d30413e1_d30414e1_d30415e1\">When a Uniface application is started, it first looks in an application-specific registry key for information, if there is one. If it can’t find it there, it looks in the default registry key.</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xhy1665702879518__li_d15374e1_d15375e1_d15376e1\">Default registry keys are stored under <span class=\"ph filepath\">HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Uniface/Uniface <var class=\"keyword varname\">Version</var>/</span>. Uniface stores logical printer definitions, command line history, and form layout state here.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xhy1665702879518__li_d15377e1_d15378e1_d15379e1\">Application-specific registry keys are stored under <span class=\"ph filepath\">HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Uniface/Uniface <var class=\"keyword varname\">Version</var>/<var class=\"keyword varname\">AppName</var>\n</span>.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xhy1665702879518__li_d15380e1_d15381e1_d15382e1\">Installation information for Uniface 10 and Uniface Router are stored under <span class=\"ph filepath\">HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/SOFTWARE/Uniface/Uniface <var class=\"keyword varname\">Version</var>/<var class=\"keyword varname\">Application</var>.</span>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"xhy1665702879518__li_d15383e1_d15384e1_d15385e1\">COM options (set with the Uniface COM\n               Configuration utility) are stored under\n                  <span class=\"ph filepath\">HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/SOFTWARE/Uniface/Uniface\n                     <var class=\"keyword varname\">Version</var>/<var class=\"keyword varname\">MyComDefinition</var></span>. </li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"xhy1665702879518__note_w7253ab1b5b1b7_w7254ab1b5b1_w7255ab1b5_w7256ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> When a Uniface\n            32-bit application is installed on a 64-bit machine, <code class=\"ph codeph\">HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE</code>\n            definitions are stored under\n                  <span class=\"ph filepath\">HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/SOFTWARE/Wow6432Node/Uniface/Uniface<var class=\"keyword varname\">Version</var>/<var class=\"keyword varname\">Application</var></span>.</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"xhy1665702879518__section_w7250ab1b5b3_w7251ab1b5_w7252ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d499323e121\">\n            \n Editing the Registry\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xhy1665702879518__p_d30419e1_d30420e1_d30421e1\">You can use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$setting</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">deletesetting</span> ProcScript instructions to read, write, and delete entries in the Registry.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"xhy1665702879518__p_d30422e1_d30423e1_d30424e1\">You can use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$setting</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">deletesetting</span> Proc instructions to read, write, and delete entries in the Registry.</p>\n<div class=\"note caution note_caution\" id=\"xhy1665702879518__note_w7257ab1b5b3b7_w7258ab1b5b3_w7259ab1b5_w7260ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">CAUTION:</span> Making changes to the Registry can significantly affect your computer,\n            so use due care when using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$setting</span> and\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">deletesetting</span>. Uniface cannot be held responsible for changes you\n            make to your Registry.</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kig1665702697791.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$setting</a><p>Retrieve, add, or change configuration settings. Depending on the platform, settings may be stored in initialization files, assignment files, environment variables, logicals, data areas, or the Windows Registry.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rur1719400533987.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>deletesetting</a><p>Delete initialization settings, environment variables, or runtime settings.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/kcb1665702670762.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Registry_Style</a><p>Controls the position of logical printers in the Microsoft Windows registry.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cgr1665702879587.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Configuring the COM Connector</a><p>The COM connector provides full COM connectivity for Uniface applications.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533742\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533742\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Uniface and the Registry Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 05, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Uniface and the Registry On Windows, Uniface saves logical printers, application layout state, command line history, and other settings in the Windows Registry. Default Registry Locations When a Uniface application is started, it first looks in an application-specific registry key for information, if there is one. If it can’t find it there, it looks in the default registry key. Default registry keys are stored under HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Uniface/Uniface Version / . Uniface stores logical printer definitions, command line history, and form layout state here. Application-specific registry keys are stored under HKEY_CURRENT_USER/Software/Uniface/Uniface Version / AppName . Installation information for Uniface 10 and Uniface Router are stored under HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/SOFTWARE/Uniface/Uniface Version / Application . COM options (set with the Uniface COM Configuration utility) are stored under HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/SOFTWARE/Uniface/Uniface Version / MyComDefinition . Note: When a Uniface 32-bit application is installed on a 64-bit machine, HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE definitions are stored under HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE/SOFTWARE/Wow6432Node/Uniface/Uniface Version / Application . Editing the Registry You can use the $setting and deletesetting ProcScript instructions to read, write, and delete entries in the Registry. You can use the $setting and deletesetting Proc instructions to read, write, and delete entries in the Registry. CAUTION: Making changes to the Registry can significantly affect your computer, so use due care when using $setting and deletesetting . Uniface cannot be held responsible for changes you make to your Registry. Related Links $setting Retrieve, add, or change configuration settings. Depending on the platform, settings may be stored in initialization files, assignment files, environment variables, logicals, data areas, or the Windows Registry. deletesetting Delete initialization settings, environment variables, or runtime settings. Registry_Style Controls the position of logical printers in the Microsoft Windows registry. Configuring the COM Connector The COM connector provides full COM connectivity for Uniface applications. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}